# General Knowledge O/X
> Everyday facts and simple trivia
@languageCode: en
// Swiq — https://swiq.jiun.dev/set/seed.en.general-knowledge.trivia/

There are seven days in a week. | O | A week is made up of seven days.
A triangle has three sides. | O | By definition, a triangle is a shape with three sides.
An adult human has about 206 bones. | O | An adult human skeleton has about 206 bones.
Honey is made by bees. | O | Bees make honey from the nectar of flowers.
The largest animal on Earth is the blue whale. | O | The blue whale is the largest animal known to have lived on Earth.
There are twelve months in a year. | O | A calendar year is divided into twelve months.
A square has five sides. | X | A square has four equal sides, not five.
Mixing blue and yellow paint makes red. | X | Mixing blue and yellow paint makes green.
Spiders have six legs. | X | Spiders have eight legs; insects have six.
There are 24 hours in a week. | X | There are 24 hours in a day; a week has 168 hours.
The freezing point of water is 100 degrees Celsius. | X | Water freezes at 0 degrees Celsius; it boils at about 100 degrees Celsius.
An adult human normally has three eyes. | X | A human normally has two eyes.
The Earth revolves around the Sun. | O | The Earth orbits the Sun, completing one full revolution in about 365 days.
Goldfish can only remember things for three seconds. | X | This is a myth; studies show goldfish can remember things for weeks or even months.
Penguins are birds. | O | Penguins are flightless birds; they have feathers and lay eggs like other birds.
The Great Wall of China is easily visible from the Moon with the naked eye. | X | This is a popular myth; the wall is far too narrow to be seen from the Moon without aid.
There are 60 minutes in an hour. | O | An hour is divided into 60 minutes, and each minute into 60 seconds.
A tomato is botanically classified as a vegetable. | X | Botanically, a tomato is a fruit because it develops from a flower and contains seeds.
Paris is the capital of France. | O | Paris is the capital and largest city of France.
Lightning never strikes the same place twice. | X | Lightning often strikes the same place repeatedly; tall buildings like the Empire State Building are hit many times a year.
Water is made of hydrogen and oxygen. | O | A water molecule (H2O) is made of two hydrogen atoms and one oxygen atom.
Ostriches bury their heads in the sand when they are scared. | X | This is a myth; ostriches may lie low or run from danger, but they do not bury their heads.
A leap year has 366 days. | O | In a leap year an extra day is added to February, giving the year 366 days instead of 365.
Bulls charge at capes because the color red makes them angry. | X | Cattle cannot distinguish red from green; it is the movement of the cape, not its color, that provokes the bull.
Bats are mammals. | O | Bats are the only mammals capable of true sustained flight; they give birth to live young and nurse them with milk.
A dozen means twenty items. | X | A dozen means twelve items; twenty items is sometimes called a score.
The Pacific is the largest ocean on Earth. | O | The Pacific Ocean is the largest and deepest ocean, covering about a third of the Earth's surface.
Bananas grow on trees. | X | Banana plants are actually giant herbaceous plants, not true trees; their 'trunk' is made of tightly packed leaf bases.
A carrot is a root vegetable. | O | The part of the carrot we eat is the plant's taproot, which grows underground.
Humans use only 10 percent of their brains. | X | This is a myth; brain scans show that virtually all parts of the brain are active over the course of a day.
A century is a period of 100 years. | O | A century means 100 years, just as a decade means 10 years.
An octagon has six sides. | X | An octagon has eight sides; a six-sided shape is called a hexagon.
An octopus has eight arms. | O | Octopuses have eight flexible arms lined with suckers.
The Statue of Liberty is located in London. | X | The Statue of Liberty stands in New York Harbor in the United States; it was a gift from France.
The human heart pumps blood around the body. | O | The heart is a muscular pump that circulates blood, carrying oxygen and nutrients throughout the body.
Antarctica is the hottest continent on Earth. | X | Antarctica is the coldest continent; the hottest average temperatures are found in Africa.
